        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Netherlandish Renaissance-Baroque ceramics styles [300106356], Netherlandish Renaissance-Baroque styles [300021051], Renaissance-Baroque regional styles [300112572], Renaissance-Baroque styles [300021033], Renaissance-Baroque styles and periods [300021031], European [300020656], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style of Dutch tin-glazed earthenware produced in Delft beginning in the mid-17th century and characterized by blue and white patterns inspired by imported Chinese porcelain.  It also refers to similar, Delft inspired wares produced in Germany and England.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de cerámica de barro vidriada con estaño holandesa producida en Delft que empieza a mediados del siglo XVII y se caracteriza por modelos azules y blancos inspirados en porcelana china importada. También se refiere a cerámicas similares, inspiradas en Delft producidas en Alemania e Inglaterra.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de stijl van Nederlands aardewerk met tinglazuur zoals gemaakt in Delft vanaf het midden van de 17de eeuw, dat zich kenmerkt door blauwwitte patronen en is geïnspireerd door geïmporteerd Chinees porselein. De term verwijst ook naar soortgelijk werk, naar het voorbeeld van Delfts aardewerk gemaakt in Duitsland en Engeland.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指始於十七世紀中葉，於代爾夫特製造的荷蘭錫釉陶器的風格，其特色為青花圖案，乃受到進口中國瓷器的影響。此辭彙亦指受到代爾夫特式陶瓷啟發，產於德國和英國的類似器皿。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
